# TOPS Pizza — VPS Claude owner-request processor
# Adjust hours for your VPS timezone if it's not UTC.
#
# Owners rarely submit changes — every 2 hours is plenty.
# A request submitted at 8 PM gets handled by 10 PM same evening; one at 9 AM
# is done by 11 AM. Adjust to */15 or */30 if you start getting frequent requests.

# Every 2 hours during business hours (11am - 11pm Calgary, MST/MDT).
# NOTE the field order: hour=11-23/2 (every 2h from 11am-11pm). The earlier
# "0 */2 11-23 * *" was wrong: it put 11-23 in the day-of-month field, so it
# only ran on days 11-23 of each month.
0 11-23/2 * * * cd /home/agent/tops-pizza-site && ./vps-claude-jobs/process-owner-requests/process.sh >> vps-claude-jobs/process-owner-requests/cron.log 2>&1

# If you'd rather only process once a day (next-day turnaround is fine for low volume),
# comment out the line above and uncomment this one:
# 0 10 * * * cd /home/agent/tops-pizza-site && ./vps-claude-jobs/process-owner-requests/process.sh >> vps-claude-jobs/process-owner-requests/cron.log 2>&1
